text: Judith Pietersen (born July 3, 1989 in Eibergen) is a Dutch volleyball player, who plays as an opposite. She is a member of the Women's National Team, and competed in the 2016 Summer Olympics. She plays for Volley Millenium Brescia. She learned playing volleyball in the garden from her cousin Caroline Wensink, with whom she played at an older age together with in the Dutch national team. ==Clubs== * Longa '59 Lichtenvoorde (2005–2008) * Martinus Amstelveen (2008–2009) * TVC Amstelveen (2009–2011) * Dresdner SC (2011–2013) * Atom Trefl Sopot (2013–2014) * Trabzon İdmanocağı (2014–2015) * Pallavolo Scandicci (2015–2016) * AGIL Volley (2016-2017) * River Volley (2017-2018) * Volley Millenium Brescia (2018-2019) ==Awards== ===Clubs=== ====National championships==== * 2016/2017 16px Italian Championship, with Igor Gorgonzola Novara ==References== ==External links== * FIVB Profile Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch women's volleyball players Category:Dutch expatriates in Italy Category:Dutch expatriates in Germany Category:People from Berkelland Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Germany Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Turkey Category:European Games competitors for the Netherlands Category:Volleyball players at the 2015 European Games Category:Volleyball players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Italy Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Poland Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Brazil Category:Dutch expatriates in Turkey Category:Dutch expatriates in Poland Category:Dutch expatriates in Brazil Category:Olympic volleyball players of the Netherlands
